  <result type="2">
   <title>
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">3. Ensuring the protection of women in prison&#x2019;s rights</narrative>
   </title>
   <reference code="265477" vocabulary="99"></reference>
   <indicator aggregation-status="0" ascending="0" measure="1">
    <title>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Assessment of achieved results: Dui Hua has contributed to promote the Bangkok Rules through its publications and exchange programmes to key Chinese officials and the general Chinese public. After years of absence to address the problems of the lack of legal protection for domestic violence victims, China&#x2019;s first Anti-Domestic Violence Law came into effect on 1 March 2016. However, the population of women in custody in China continues to rise; the Asian Pacific Conference on Correctional Administrators found that by the middle of 2015, China had more than 107,000 women in prison, which was an increase of 3,2 percent from the previous year, making it even more relevant to promote and protect the rights of female prisoners.</narrative>
    </title>
