  <result type="2">
   <title>
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">4. Ensuring the protection of prisoners sentenced to death&#x2019;s rights</narrative>
   </title>
   <reference code="265478" vocabulary="99"></reference>
   <indicator aggregation-status="0" ascending="0" measure="1">
    <title>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Assessment of achieved results: By publicising estimates of annual executions carried out in China, Dui Hua has provided transparency to the practice of capital punishment in China. Based on its internal death penalty log, Dui Hua has calculated that the average length of waiting time from the death sentence to execution is two months. This period, which is longer than originally expected, provides those seeking to intervene in death penalty cases a window to carry out intervention and advocacy.</narrative>
    </title>
