  <result type="2">
   <title>
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">2. Ensuring the protection of juvenile offenders&#x2019; rights</narrative>
   </title>
   <reference code="265476" vocabulary="99"></reference>
   <indicator aggregation-status="0" ascending="0" measure="1">
    <title>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Assessment of achieved results: Dui Hua has contributed to the reform of the juvenile justice system in China through its exchange programmes by generating recommendations from American leading experts and increasing the awareness of best practices in the juvenile justice system among Chinese stakeholders. Non-custodial measures are crucial in minimising the chance of recidivism among juveniles, in ensuring their healthy development and facilitating their positive interaction with the community. According to China&#x2019;s official compendium on juvenile justice and information gathered from Dui Hua interlocutors, courts sentenced 48 percent of juveniles to non-custodial measures and other punishment-exemption measures in 2015, which is an increase 41,7 percent in 2012 and 36 percent in 2010.</narrative>
    </title>
