  <result type="2">
   <title>
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Ensuring the protection of political and religious detainees and prisoners&#x2019; rights</narrative>
   </title>
   <reference code="265475" vocabulary="99"></reference>
   <indicator aggregation-status="0" ascending="0" measure="1">
    <title>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Assessment of achieved results: Dui Hua conducts research by using open Chinese sources and PPDB is the world&#x2019;s most comprehensive database of Chinese prisoners of conscience. Access to the PPDB is of significant value for Denmark to track personal cases, which are i.e. raised by Danish politicians. During Dui Hua&#x2019;s exchanges with Chinese interlocutors, advocacy on behalf of prisoners of conscience have been carried out. Dui Hua is also the only organisation to successfully hand over prisoner lists to the Chinese government (973 names in 2014-2017) and receive written responses in return (193 names in 2014-2017) since 2012. Dui Hua also provides the lists handed by the EU to the China during the annual EU-China Human Rights dialogues. Additionally, 152 prisoner cases have been granted acts of clemency or better treatment on the prisoners list between 2014-2017, and 2,155 media mentions of Dui Hua&#x2019;s research and publication has been registered, contributing to greater awareness.</narrative>
    </title>
